      <item>
        <title>Variance</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Measures the variance of a series of values around their mean value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;Var(X)=\frac{1}{N}\sum_i{(X_i-\bar{X})^2}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\bar{X}=\frac{1}{N}*\sum_i{X_i}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The variance can be computed incrementally:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;Var(X)=\bar{X^2}-(\bar{X}*\bar{X})&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, we sum all &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;X_i&lt;/script&gt; and all &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;X_i^2&lt;/script&gt;, then build the difference of their
mean values.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
