      <item>
        <title>Tracking error</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;The tracking error of a portfolio is defined as the annualized standard
deviation of its excess returns over a benchmark.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;\alpha =( r_{Pf} - r_{Bm})&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;TE = sqrt{\sum{(\alpha_i - \bar{\alpha})^2}}&lt;/script&gt;

</description>
