      <item>
        <title>Put-call parity</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;For European calls and puts their prices are related by the Put-call parity:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;p + S_0e^{-qT} = c + Ke^{-rT}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;p&lt;/script&gt; and &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;c&lt;/script&gt; are the prices of the put, call options and &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;S&lt;/script&gt; is the
current spot price of the underlying, &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;K&lt;/script&gt; the strike price, &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;T&lt;/script&gt; the time to
maturity. The interest rate is integrated with &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;r&lt;/script&gt; and &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;q&lt;/script&gt; denotes the
dividend yield on the stock.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
